HEADWORD: Oscillaria
<hw>Os`cil*la"ri*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. L. <ets>oscillare</ets> to swing.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
genus of dark green, or purplish black, filamentous, fresh-water algae,
the threads of which have an automatic swaying or crawling motion.
Called also <altname>Oscillatoria</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

